Pre-requisites:

JDK, Eclipse, WebDriver(selenium standalone jar file), browser, application to be tested.

Steps to install selenium webdriver:


Step:1 - Download and install the Java Software Development Kit (JDK)
Step: 2 - Download and install latest version of "Eclipse IDE for Java Developers" 
Step: 3- Download Selenium Webdriver for Java Client Driver
Step 4 - Configure Eclipse IDE with WebDriver by following the below steps:
      * Launch the "eclipse.exe" file inside the "eclipse" folder that we extracted in step 2. 
      * When asked to select for a workspace, just accept the default location.
      * Create a new project through File > New > Java Project. Name the project as "newproject".
        A new pop-up window will open enter the below details: 
          Project Name
          Location to save project
          Select an execution JRE
          Select layout project option
          Click on Finish button
Step 5:
Once step 4 finished right-click on the newly created project and Select New > Package, and name that package as "newpackage"
Step 6:
A pop-up window will open to name the package. Here enter the name of the package and click on Finish button
Step 7:
Create a new Java class under newpackage by right-clicking on it and then selecting- New > Class, and then name it  
Step 8:
Now add the external jars by right clicking on the new project and select properties. Then go to java buildpath->Libraries tab-> Add external jars button 
Step 9: After adding the jarfiles click OK



